   "source": [
    "Assignments in Mutable Sequences - Lecture"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "42f1d3fd-f2e6-49bc-b2fa-dafe0139cf16",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Assigning Values via Indexes, Slices, and Extended Slices\n",
    "\n",
    "We have seen how tyo extract elememts from a sequence using indexing, slciing, and extended slicing\n",
    "\n",
    "[i]\n",
    "[i:j] slice(i, j)\n",
    "[i:j:k] slice(i, j, k) k != 1 (if k=1 then standard slice)\n",
    "\n",
    "Mutable sequences support assignments via a specific index and they support assignment via slices\n",
    "The value being assigned via slicing/extended slicing must be an iterable (any iterable, not just a sequence type)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "43893cfc-bae7-4926-b579-f263fa3946f8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Replacing a Slice\n",
    "\n",
    "A slice can be replaced with another iterable\n",
    "For regular slices (non-extended), the slice and iterable need not be the same length\n",
    "\n",
    "l = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
    "l[1:3] -> [2, 3]\n",
    "l[1:3] = (10, 20, 30)\n",
    "l -> [1, 10, 20, 30, 4, 5]\n",
    "\n",
    "The list l was mutated, id(l) did not change.\n",
    "With extended slicing the, extended slice and iterable must have the same length\n",
    "\n",
    "l = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
    "l[0:4:2] -> [1, 3]\n",
    "l[0:4:2] = [10, 30]\n",
    "l -> [10, 2, 30, 4, 5]\n",
    "\n",
    "The list l was mutated, id(l) did not change."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "d8282549-b9f1-49c3-8f32-0c0b12a7d40d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Deleting a Slice\n",
    "\n",
    "Deletion is just a special case of replacement\n",
    "We simply assign an empty ioterable -> works for standard slicing only (extended replacement needs same length)\n",
    "\n",
    "l = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
    "l[1:3] -> [2, 3]\n",
    "l[2:3] = []\n",
    "l -> [1, 4, 5]\n",
    "\n",
    "The list l was mutated."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "3f0e52ca-ca76-4abf-98ee-1086f39f7d6d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Insertions using Slices\n",
    "\n",
    "We can insert element using slice assignment. Trick is that slice must be empty, otherwise it would replace the elements in the slice.\n",
    "\n",
    "l = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
    "l[1:1] -> []\n",
    "l[1:1] = 'abc'\n",
    "l -> [1, 'a', 'b', 'c', 2, 3, 4, 5]\n",
    "\n",
    "The list l was mutated.\n",
    "Obviously will not work with extended slices, they require lengths to be the same."
   ]
  }
 ],
